---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Jared Street" description="About Jared Street, software developer and recent computer programming graduate.">
  <section class="page-hero fade-in">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About Me</h1>
    <p>
      I am a software developer focused on building practical applications with C#, ASP.NET Core,
      PHP, SQL, JavaScript, and Go.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section-card fade-in">
    <div class="hero-card">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="eyebrow">Background</p>
        <h2>Developer with a practical, project-first mindset</h2>

        <p class="hero-summary">
          I recently completed my Computer Programming degree and have been building projects across
          web development, databases, desktop tooling, APIs, and game prototypes. I like projects that
          solve a concrete problem, even when they are small.
        </p>

        <p>
          My strongest interests are application development, backend logic, database-backed systems,
          and tools, and business applications. I am especially interested in entry-level software
          development roles where I can keep improving through real code, feedback, and production
          practices.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="hero-photo-wrap">
        <img
          class="hero-photo"
          src="/screenshots/tempheadshot1.jpg"
          alt="Headshot of Jared Street"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section-card fade-in">
    <p class="eyebrow">Technical Focus</p>
    <h2>What I Like Building</h2>

    <div class="project-grid">
      <article class="project-card">
        <h3>Web Applications</h3>
        <p>
          Database-backed applications with authentication, CRUD workflows, validation, and clear user flows.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span class="tech-pill">C#</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">ASP.NET Core</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">PHP</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">MySQL</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">SQL Server</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <article class="project-card">
        <h3>APIs & Services</h3>
        <p>
          REST-style services, JSON responses, AJAX clients, and projects where frontend behavior depends
          on structured backend data.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
          <span class="tech-pill">REST</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">JSON</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">AJAX</span>
          <span class="tech-pill">JavaScript</span>
        </div>
      </article>

        <article class="project-card">
        <h3>MVC Applications</h3>
        <p>
            Web applications built around clear controller actions, model validation, database-backed workflows,
            and maintainable separation between data, logic, and views.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
            <span class="tech-pill">C#</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">ASP.NET Core MVC</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">Entity Framework</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">SQL Server</span>
        </div>
        </article>

        <article class="project-card">
        <h3>C# Applications</h3>
        <p>
            Application projects focused on object-oriented design, user workflows, state management,
            and practical problem solving across desktop, web, and interactive systems.
        </p>

        <div class="tech-list">
            <span class="tech-pill">C#</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">.NET</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">OOP</span>
            <span class="tech-pill">Application Logic</span>
        </div>
        </article>
    </div>
    <p>And others. I am always willing to learn new technologies and approaches!</p>
  </section>
  
    <section class="section-card fade-in outside-code-section">
      <div class="outside-code-layout">
        <div class="outside-code-main">
          <p class="eyebrow">Outside the Code</p>

          <p>
            For hobbies, I enjoy reading, strength training, and playing video games.
          </p>

          <p>
            When reading, I heavily enjoy anything fantasy, technical books, and classic literature.
            My favorite series is
            <a
              href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Malazan_Book_of_the_Fallen"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
              Malazan Book of the Fallen
            </a>
            by Steven Erikson.
          </p>

          <p>
            I’m also into strength training, although I have not been as consistent with it lately as I would like.
            My discipline of choice is powerlifting.
          </p>

          <figure class="outside-code-cat">
            <img
              class="outside-code-cat"
              src="/screenshots/salem.png"
              alt="My cat Salem"
            />  
            <figcaption>This is Salem!</figcaption>
          </figure>

          <div class="button-row">
            <a class="button button-primary" href="/projects/">View My Projects</a>
            <a class="button button-secondary" href="/documents/JaredStreetResume.pdf">View Resume</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <aside class="fun-fact-card">
          <p class="eyebrow">Fun Fact</p>
          <h3>STRAFTAT</h3>

          <p>
            There is this FPS game I play competitively as a hobby,
            <a
              href="https://store.steampowered.com/app/2386720/STRAFTAT/"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
            >
            STRAFTAT.
            </a>
          Tournaments are hosted on weekends, some with prizepools. I attend these here and there. I am top 100 in the world leaderboards.<span>&#128526;</span>
          </p>

          <img
            class="fun-fact-image"
            src="/screenshots/aboubi.png"
            alt="STRAFTAT screenshot"
          />
        </aside>
      </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>